history.content:
Seems pretty unlikely that you will get into CS182 if you are 148 on the waitlist. If you have other classes that you want to take, probably should drop from the waitlist.

A 2-tech semester would be fairly light compared to a 3-tech semester, especially given that ee127/cs189 are both significantly more difficult than cs170 and at least equal to if not more difficult than ee126. 

This is Prof Ranade's first semester teaching ee127 so there is little prior data. However historically ee127 has been made more difficult because of the poor course staff, and Prof Ranade is an incredible prof who is always very involved with course staff so it should make ee127 a bit easier.

You seem very ahead already. Perhaps you can afford to not take cs188 and dedicate more focus to ee127 and cs189.

my background: 2nd-year CS major who wants to study AI/ML; have taken cs61ab70 ee16ab ds100;  this semester took cs170, ee126, and a breadth and got As (fa2018) 

CS182 is currently 187/187 and 148 on the waitlist, am i likely to get in the class at this point? Is it even worth taking?  

edit: CS 182/282A – Enroll into the lecture and 999 section. Class webcast but not likely to expand past room capacity.

How does ee127, cs188, and cs189 (Ranade/Bayan, Levine/Russel, Shewchuck) compare in difficulty and workload to the above semester?  Should I add on math110, or a breadth? How hard/different are classes with Ranade? (For ee127) 

Thanks :)
